trans-unit.source: Encapsulates a collection of objects for use by the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown"></xref> class.

To create a collection of objects to display in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown> control, you can add or remove the items individually by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Add%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Remove%2A> methods.
The collection is accessed from the parent control, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown>, by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.Items%2A> property.
Adds the specified object to the end of the collection.
You can also add a new <xref:System.Object> to the collection by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Insert%2A> method.

To remove an <xref:System.Object> that you have previously added, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Remove%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.RemoveAt%2A> methods.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to be added to the end of the collection.
The zero-based index value of the <xref href="System.Object"></xref> added to the collection.
Inserts the specified object into the collection at the specified location.
You can also add a new <xref:System.Object> to the collection by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Add%2A> method.

To remove an <xref:System.Object> that you have previously added, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Remove%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.RemoveAt%2A> methods.
The indexed location within the collection to insert the <xref href="System.Object"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to insert.
Gets or sets the item at the specified indexed location in the collection.

To assign items to a specific location, or to retrieve them from the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection>, you can reference the collection object with a specific index value.
The index value of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection> is a zero-based index.
The indexed location of the item in the collection.
An <xref href="System.Object"></xref> that represents the item at the specified indexed location.
Removes the specified item from the collection.
You can also remove an <xref:System.Object> that you have previously added by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.RemoveAt%2A> method.

To add a new <xref:System.Object> to the collection, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Insert%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Add%2A> methods.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to remove from the collection.
Removes the item from the specified location in the collection.
You can also remove an <xref:System.Object> that you have previously added by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Remove%2A> method.

To add a new <xref:System.Object> to the collection, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Insert%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DomainUpDown.DomainUpDownItemCollection.Add%2A> methods.
The indexed location of the <xref href="System.Object"></xref> in the collection.
